    "infoText": "Testimony of Aleksander Bartal, born in Pabianice, Poland, 1927, regarding his experiences in the Pabianice Ghetto, Lodz Ghetto and Auschwitz, Mauthausen and Gusen camps\r\n\r\nHis childhood.\r\n\r\nGerman occupation; deportation to the Pabianice Ghetto, February 1940; labor in a sewing workshop; liquidation of the ghetto, May 1942; selection; march to the Lodz Ghetto; labor unloading wooden boards from trains; labor in a clothing factory; curfew (Sperre) \"Aktion\", September 1942; ghetto life; activities in Hashomer Hatzair; raises vegetables; liquidation of the ghetto, summer 1944; deportation to Auschwitz for six weeks, August 1944; selection; transfer to Mauthausen by train; labor dragging rocks from a quarry; labor in Gusen II repairing dirt paths; labor unloading in St. Georgen; illness; stay in the sick barracks in Mauthausen; death of his father; liberation, 05 May 1945.\r\n\r\nConvalescence; aliya to Eretz Israel via Italy with help from the Jewish Brigade, November 1945.",
